Manchester United midfielder, Donny van de Beek’s new club has finally been revealed. According to football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, Van de Beek has agreed to a deal to join Everton on loan from Man United. Romano made this known in a tweet via his Twitter handle on Sunday. He tweeted: “Donny van de Beek to Everton, done deal and confirmed! The decision has been made, here we go. Donny confirmed few minutes ago his choice to Frank Lampard. “Everton joined the race yesterday, as revealed. They will cover full salary until June plus loan fee.” Van de Beek joined Manchester United from Ajax in 2020. The Dutch star is still struggling for game time under interim boss Ralf Rangnick as his future at Old Trafford continues to be in doubt.